[{"client_msg_id":"11fa9b1e-00b5-4907-91cd-c77a1ed0bdcc","type":"message","text":"Hey: Is there a proper way to \"merge\" a vector of `@view` s into a single one?","user":"U01MG0TN079","ts":"1616407021.359900","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"D37A8","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Hey: Is there a proper way to \"merge\" a vector of "},{"type":"text","text":"@view","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" s into a single one?"}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1616407021.359900","reply_count":4,"reply_users_count":2,"latest_reply":"1616408210.360800","reply_users":["U7HAYKY9X","U01MG0TN079"],"is_locked":false,"subscribed":false},{"client_msg_id":"b6b60425-1b7f-4ffe-97a1-7fa630ee7793","type":"message","text":"Not possible, unless they are all contiguous in memory. I.e. suppose you have the following vector (pretend they're views):\n```[ \n  a[2:3]\n  a[5:7]\n]```\nHow should the resulting merged view be represented in memory? `a[2:7]` ? That's wrong. `a[[2,3,5,6,7]]` ? Then it's no longer a view","user":"U7HAYKY9X","ts":"1616407173.360200","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"nGVrb","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Not possible, unless they are all contiguous in memory. I.e. suppose you have the following vector (pretend they're views):\n"}]},{"type":"rich_text_preformatted","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"[ \n  a[2:3]\n  a[5:7]\n]"}]},{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"How should the resulting merged view be represented in memory? "},{"type":"text","text":"a[2:7]","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" ? That's wrong. "},{"type":"text","text":"a[[2,3,5,6,7]]","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" ? Then it's no longer a view"}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1616407021.359900","parent_user_id":"U01MG0TN079"},{"client_msg_id":"5cfcd2a7-96c7-42a0-9e39-929c9d1483c2","type":"message","text":"Makes sense. Essentially, what I want is a \"lazy\" iterator I guess","user":"U01MG0TN079","ts":"1616407524.360400","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"0mOB","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Makes sense. Essentially, what I want is a \"lazy\" iterator I guess"}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1616407021.359900","parent_user_id":"U01MG0TN079"},{"client_msg_id":"8526e6ef-305f-43fe-81d2-02c54acf722e","type":"message","text":"Iterators.flatten","user":"U7HAYKY9X","ts":"1616408016.360600","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"PRV","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Iterators.flatten"}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1616407021.359900","parent_user_id":"U01MG0TN079"},{"client_msg_id":"198496ba-5702-490e-a52b-b62770c3bdd1","type":"message","text":"great, thanks!","user":"U01MG0TN079","ts":"1616408210.360800","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"Qxos","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"great, thanks!"}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1616407021.359900","parent_user_id":"U01MG0TN079"}]